value: <l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">[illeg.] this to some of the early songs:</l>

<quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" source="#" rend="block">
            <l>Summer is icumen in,</l>
            <l>Lhude sing cuccu...</l>
          </quote>

<quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" source="#" rend="block">
            <l>Bytwene Mersh and Averil,</l>
            <l>When spray biginneth to springe,</l>
            <l>The lutel foul hath hire wyl</l>
            <l>On <del>her</del> [lyfe?] lud to synge</l>
          </quote>

<quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" source="#" rend="block"> <!-- check this against possible source texts! -->
            <l>When the nythegale singes</l>
            <l>The wodes wayen grene,</l>
            <l>Lef art gras ant blosme;</l>
            <l>The ancye, I wene</l>
            <l>....</l>
            <l>Ich hav loved al this yer</l>
            <l>That I may love namore</l>
            <l>Ich have liked monie & oft</l>
            <l>Lemmore, for this ore...</l>
          </quote>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">That is <del>the voice of</del> <rs type="person" ref="../resources/annotations.xml#psn-anon" key="Anon">Anon</rs>, singing out of doors,</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><del>singing</del> because love & spring make him vocal; </l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">but <del>he, or she, has</del> But who listens? <del>What was</del></l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><del>the</del> <del>the first songs were sung</del> If once the song is</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">sung to be heard, it was one of the <add>of the few</add> of the innumerable</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><del>This the [literature?] that</del></l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Somebody heard that particular song, or it</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">would not be heard to day for the words were</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">written down: <del>He</del> <add place="above">She</add> had an audience; but</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">no name. <del>The song was therefore unattached</del> <add place="above">[He was?] no longer singing, for this [written?] down.</add></l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><del>singer.</del> <del>And</del> <del>so was</del> Anonymous</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">singing <del>therefore</del> differs from all other singing.</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">But <del>also</del> <add>later [illeg.] it has now become words</add> this writing differs from all other</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">writing because it is not attached to a person.</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Anon is only a voice. He  has his representative today; <del>to</del></l>
